{"title_page": "Dale River (Boyne)", "text_new": "{{short description|River}}\n{{Infobox river|name=Dale River|image=|image_caption=|source1_location=[[County Westmeath|Westmeath]] and [[County Meath]]|mouth_location=}}\nThe '''Dale River''' is a river that flows through [[County Westmeath]] and [[County Meath]] [[Ireland]]. The rivers source is at [[Lough Lene]], it then flows for 19 miles before meeting the [[River Boyne]], meeting it near the town of [[Clonard, County Meath]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Joyce|first=Patrick Weston|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S9oHAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA158&lpg=PA158&dq=River+Dale+meets+the+Boyne&source=bl&ots=bNGSK5HQvX&sig=ACfU3U2EIsAegnSoBQw4ufBFcTjpT1IrkA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjm4Pn77N3oAhUJPK0KHR1NA7AQ6AEwAHoECBAQKw#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The geography of the counties of Ireland|date=1883|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Westmeath|url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/1911_Encyclop%C3%A6dia_Britannica/Westmeath|work=1911 Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|volume=Volume 28|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.libraryireland.com/Atlas/Meath.php|title=Meath|website=www.libraryireland.com|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Rivers of County Meath]]\n[[Category:Rivers of County Westmeath]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|River}}\n{{Infobox river|name=Dale River|image=|image_caption=|source1_location=[[County Westmeath|Westmeath]] and [[County Meath]]|mouth_location=}}\nThe '''Dale River''' is a river that flows through[[County Westmeath]], and [[County Meath]] [[Ireland]]. The rivers source is at [[Lough Lene]], it then flows for 19 miles before meeting the [[River Boyne]], meeting it near the town of [[Clonard, County Meath]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Joyce|first=Patrick Weston|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=S9oHAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA158&lpg=PA158&dq=River+Dale+meets+the+Boyne&source=bl&ots=bNGSK5HQvX&sig=ACfU3U2EIsAegnSoBQw4ufBFcTjpT1IrkA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjm4Pn77N3oAhUJPK0KHR1NA7AQ6AEwAHoECBAQKw#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The geography of the counties of Ireland|date=1883|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Westmeath|url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/1911_Encyclop%C3%A6dia_Britannica/Westmeath|work=1911 Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|volume=Volume 28|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.libraryireland.com/Atlas/Meath.php|title=Meath|website=www.libraryireland.com|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Rivers of County Meath]]\n[[Category:Rivers of County Westmeath]]\n", "name_user": "Ww2censor", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Spelling/grammar/punctuation/typographical correction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dale_River_(Boyne)"}
{"title_page": "List of Real Madrid CF records and statistics", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n[[File:Cristiano Ajax.jpg|thumb|185px|[[Cristiano Ronaldo]], pictured here in September 2011, is [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s all-time leading goalscorer with 451 goals in all competitions.|alt=A man in a white shirt and shorts looking upwards.]]\n[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol]] is a Spanish professional [[association football]] club based in [[Madrid]]. The club was formed in 1902 as ''Madrid Football Club'', and played its first competitive match on [[1902 Copa de la Coronaci\u00f3n|13 May 1902]], when it entered the semi-final of the [[Copa del Rey|Campeonato de Copa de S.M. Alfonso XIII]].<ref name=\"Real Madrid turns 106 (I)\">{{cite web | title = Pre-history and first official title (1900\u20131910) | url = http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/en/1202730681095/noticia/Noticia/Real_Madrid_turns_106_(I).htm | publisher = Realmadrid.com | accessdate = 12 July 2008 | author = Lu\u00eds Miguel Gonz\u00e1lez | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081229094130/http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/en/1202730681095/noticia/Noticia/Real_Madrid_turns_106_%28I%29.htm | archivedate = 29 December 2008 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> Real Madrid currently plays in the Spanish La Liga. Real Madrid was one of the founding members of La Liga in [[1929 La Liga|1929]], and is one of three clubs, including [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and [[Athletic Bilbao]], never to have been relegated from the league. They have also been involved in European football ever since they became the first Spanish club to enter the European Cup in 1955, except for the 1977\u201378 and [[1996\u201397 Real Madrid CF season|1996\u201397]] seasons.\n\nThis list encompasses the major honours won by Real Madrid and records set by the club, their managers and their players. The player records section includes details of the club's leading goalscorers and those who have made most appearances in first-team competitions. It also records notable achievements by Real Madrid players on the international stage, and the highest transfer fees paid and received by the club.\n\nThe club currently holds the record for the most [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup / UEFA Champions League]] triumphs with 13, and the most La Liga titles with 33. Real Madrid is also the most successful club in international titles with 26, more than any team in the world. The club's record appearance maker is [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]], who made 741 appearances from 1994 to 2010; the club's record goalscorer is Portuguese ace [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], who has 450 goals in all competitions.\n\n== Players ==\n{{See also|List of Real Madrid CF players}}\n\n=== Appearances ===\n''Competitive, professional matches only. Bold indicates player is still active at club level.''\n''As of 8 March 2020''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; width:70%;\"\n!!!Name!!Years!![[La Liga|League]]!![[Copa del Rey|Cup]]!!Europe{{ref label|Europe|A|}}!!Other{{ref label|Other|B|}}!!Total\n|-\n|1||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]]||1994\u20132010||550||37||132||22||'''741'''\n|-\n|2||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Iker Casillas]]||1999\u20132015||510||40||152||23||'''725'''\n|-\n|3||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Manuel Sanch\u00eds Hontiyuelo|Manuel Sanch\u00eds]]||1983\u20132001||523||67||100||20||'''710'''\n|-\n|4||{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Santillana (footballer)|Santillana]]||1971\u20131988||461||84||87||13||'''645'''\n|-\n|5||{{flagicon|ESP}} '''[[Sergio Ramos]]'''||2005\u2013''present''||445||48||124||24||'''640'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|6||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Fernando Hierro]]||1989\u20132003||439||43||103||16||'''601'''\n|-\n||{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Francisco Gento]]||1953\u20131971||428||74||95||4||'''601'''\n|-\n|8||{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Jos\u00e9 Antonio Cama