20131''' v [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], 14 December 1947\n*First competitive match at Santiago Bernab\u00e9u: '''3\u20131''' v [[RCD Espanyol|Espa\u00f1ol]], [[1947\u201348 La Liga]], 18 December 1947\n*First [[Small Club World Cup]] match: '''3\u20132''' v [[La Salle FC|La Salle]], [[1952 Small Club World Cup]], (Group stage), 13 July 1952\n*First [[Latin Cup]] match: '''2\u20130''' v [[C.F. Os Belenenses|Belenenses]], 1952 Latin Cup, (Semi-final), 22 May 1955\n*First [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] match: '''2\u20130''' v [[Servette FC|Servette]], [[1955\u201356 European Cup]], (Round 1 \u2013 First leg), 8 September 1955\n*First [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]] match: '''0\u20130''' v [[C.A. Pe\u00f1arol|Pe\u00f1arol]], [[1960 Intercontinental Cup]], (First leg), 3 July 1960\n*First [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]] match: '''0\u20130''' v [[Hibernians F.C.]], [[1970\u201371 European Cup Winners' Cup|1970\u201371 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]], (Round 1 \u2013 First leg), 17 September 1970\n*First [[UEFA Cup]] match: '''2\u20131''' v [[FC Basel|Basel]], [[1971\u201372 UEFA Cup]], (Round 1 \u2013 First leg), 15 September 1971\n*First [[UEFA Champions League]] match: '''0\u20131''' v [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[1995\u201396 UEFA Champions League]], (Group stage), 13 September 1995\n*First [[UEFA Super Cup]] match: '''0\u20131''' v [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[1998 UEFA Super Cup]],  28 August 1998\n*First [[FIFA Club World Cup]] match: '''3\u20131''' v [[Al-Nassr]], [[2000 FIFA Club World Championship]], (Group stage), 5 January 2000\n\n==== Record wins ====\n*Record League win: '''11\u20132''' against [[Elche CF|Elche]] (during  [[1959\u201360 La Liga]]).\n*Record Cup win: '''11\u20131''' against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] (during the [[1942\u201343 Copa del Rey]]).\n*Record European win: '''9\u20130''' against [[Boldklubben 1913|B 1913]] (during the [[1961\u201362 European Cup]]).\n*Record home win: '''11\u20132''' against [[Elche CF|Elche]] (during  [[1959\u201360 La Liga]]).\n* Record away win: '''7\u20131''' against [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] (during [[1987\u201388 La Liga]]), '''8\u20132''' against [[Deportivo de La Coru\u00f1a|Deportivo La Coru\u00f1a]] (during [[2014\u201315 La Liga]]).\n\n==== Record defeats ====\n*Record League defeat:\n::'''1\u20138''' against [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] (during [[1929\u201330 La Liga]]).\n*Record Cup defeat:\n::'''0\u20136''' against [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] (during the [[1998\u201399 Copa del Rey]]).\n*Record European defeat:\n::'''0\u20135''' against [[1. FC Kaiserslautern]] (during the [[1981\u201382 UEFA Cup]]).\n::'''0\u20135''' against [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] (during the  [[1988\u201389 European Cup]]).\n*Record home defeat: '''0\u20136''' against [[Athletic Bilbao|Athletic Club]] (during [[1930\u201331 La Liga]]).\n*Record away defeat: '''1\u20138''' against [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] (during [[1929\u201330 La Liga]]).\n\n==== Streaks ====\n*Longest unbeaten run (all major competitions): '''40 matches''' (from [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]] quarter-finals first leg to day 16 [[2016\u201317 La Liga|2016\u20132017]] season).\n*Longest unbeaten run (League): '''28 matches''' (from day 27 [[2015\u201316 La Liga|2015\u201316]] season, to day 16 [[2016\u201317 La Liga|2016\u201317]] season).\n*Longest unbeaten home run (League): '''121 matches''' (from [[1956\u201357 La Liga|1956\u201357]] season, to [[1964\u201365 La Liga|1964\u201365]] season).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/unbeaten.html#home |title=Unbeaten at Home in the League |publisher=Rsssf.com |date= |accessdate=25 September 2013}}</ref>\n*Longest unbeaten away run (League): '''13 matches''' (from day 23 [[2016\u201317 La Liga|2016\u201317]] season, to day 8 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).\n*Longest unbeaten run from the first match of season (League): '''28 matches''' ([[1988\u201389 La Liga|1988\u201389]] season).\n*Longest winning streak (all major competitions): '''22 matches''' ([[2014\u201315 Real Madrid CF season|2014\u201315]] season).\n*Longest winning streak (League): '''16 matches''' (from day 27 [[2015\u201316 La Liga|2015\u201316]] season, to day 4 [[2016\u201317 La Liga|2016\u201317]] season).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/spanish-primera-division/15/blog/post/2954256/real-madrid-perfect-barcelona-net-five-valencia-rock-bottom-of-la-liga |title=Real Madrid perfect, Barcelona & Atleti net five, Valencia bottom of La Liga |publisher=espnfc.com |access-date=19 September 2016}}</ref>\n*Longest winning home streak (League): '''31 matches''' (from day 36 [[1987\u201388 La Liga|1987\u201388]] season, to day 28 [[1988\u201389 La Liga|1988\u201389]] season).\n*Longest winning away streak (League): '''13 matches''' (from day 23 [[2016\u201317 La Liga|2016\u201317]] season, to day 8 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).\n*Longest winning streak from the first match of season (League): '''9 matches''' ([[1968\u201369 La Liga|1968\u201369]] season).\n*Longest drawing streak (League): '''4 matches''' ([[2006\u201307 La Liga|2006\u201307]] season).\n*Longest losing streak (League): '''5 matches''' ([[2003\u201304 La Liga|2003\u201304]] season, [[2008\u201309 La Liga|2008\u201309]] season).\n*Longest streak without a win (League): '''9 matches''' ([[1984\u201385 La Liga|1984\u201385]] season).\n*Longest scoring run (all major competitions): '''73 matches''' (from [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League]] semi-finals first leg, to day 4 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2017/05/real-madrid-match-61-game-scoring-record|title=Real Madrid beat record with 73-game scoring streak {{!}} Real Madrid CF|work=Real Madrid CF - Web Oficial|access-date=21 May 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n*Longest scoring run (League): '''54 matches''' (from day 27 [[2015-16 La Liga|2015\u201316]] season, to day 4 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).\n*Longest scoring home run (League): '''26 matches''' (from day 28 [[2015-16 La Liga|2015\u201316]] season, to day 3 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).\n*Longest scoring away run (League): '''35 matches''' (from day 18 [[2015-16 La Liga|2015\u201316]] season, to day 10 [[2017\u201318 La Liga|2017\u201318]] season).\n*Longest non-scoring run (League): '''3 matches''' ([[2001\u201302 La Liga|2001\u201302]] season).\n*Longest streak without conceding a goal (League): '''7 matches''' ([[1997\u201398 La Liga|1997\u201398]] season).\n\n=== Wins/draws/losses in a season ===\n*Most league wins in a season: '''32''' in 38 games (during the [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season).\n*Most league home wins in a season: '''18''' in 19 games (during [[1987\u201388 La Liga|1987\u201388]] and [[2009\u201310 La Liga|2009\u201310]] seasons).\n*Most league away wins in a season: '''16''' in 19 games (during the [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season).\n*Most league draws in a season: '''15''' in 34 games (during the [[1978\u201379 La Liga|1978\u201379]] season).\n*Most league defeats in a season: '''13''' in 34 games (during the [[1973\u201374 La Liga|1973\u201374]] season).\n*Fewest league wins in a season: '''7''' in 18 games (during the [[1929\u201330 La Liga|1929\u201330]] season).\n*Fewest league draws in a season:\n** '''1''' in 18 games (during the [[1929 La Liga|1929]] season).\n** '''1''' in 22 games (during the [[1934\u201335 La Liga|1934\u201335]] and [[1939\u201340 La Liga|1939\u201340]] season).\n*Fewest league defeats in a season: '''0''' in 18 games (during the [[1931\u201332 La Liga|1931\u201332]] season).\n\n=== Goals ===\n*Most league goals scored in a season: '''121''' (during the [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season).\n*Most goals scored in a season in all competitions: '''174''' (during the [[2011\u201312 Real Madrid CF season|2011\u201312]] season).\n* Best goal difference in a League season: '''+89''' in [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season.\n*Fewest league goals scored in a season: '''24''' (during the [[1930\u201331 La Liga|1930\u201331]] season).\n*Most league goals conceded in a season: '''71''' (during the [[1950\u201351 La Liga|1950\u201351]] season).\n*Fewest league goals conceded in a season: '''15''' (during the [[1931\u201332 La Liga|1931\u201332]] season).\n\n=== Points ===\n*Most points in a season:\n**Two points for a win: '''66''' in 44 matches (during the [[1986\u201387 La Liga|1986\u201387]] season).\n**Three points for a win: '''100''' in 38 matches (during the [[2011\u201312 La Liga|2011\u201312]] season).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hispanicallyspeakingnews.com/latino-daily-news/details/fc-barcelona-ties-real-madrids-record-of-100-points/24879/ |title=Real Madrid record of 100 points a season |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003202053/http://www.hispanicallyspeakingnews.com/latino-daily-news/details/fc-barcelona-ties-real-madrids-record-of-100-points/24879/ |archivedate=3 October 2015 }}</ref>\n*Fewest points in a season:\n**Two points for a win: '''17''' in 18 matches (during the [[1929\u201330 La Liga|1929\u201330]] season).\n**Three points for a win: '''70''' in 42 matches (during the [[1995\u201396 La Liga|1995\u201396]] season).\n\n== Season-by-season performance ==\n{{Main|List of Real Madrid CF seasons}}\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{refbegin}}\n:A.&nbsp;{{note|Europe}} The \"Europe\" column constitutes goals and appearances in the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup / UEFA Champions League]], [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup]], [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup / UEFA Europa League]] and [[UEFA Intertoto Cup]].\n:B.&nbsp;{{note|Other}} The \"Other\" column constitutes goals and appearances in the [[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]], the [[Copa de la Liga]], the [[UEFA Super Cup]], the [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]] and the [[FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Championship]].\n{{refend}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Real Madrid}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Real Madrid CF Statistics}}\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF|Statistics]]\n[[Category:Spanish football club statistics]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF-related lists|Records]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{refimprove|date=January 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n[[File:Cristiano Ajax.jpg|thumb|185px|[[Cristiano Ronaldo]], pictured here in September 2011, is [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s all-time leading goalscorer with 451 goals in all competitions.|alt=A man in a white shirt and shorts looking upwards.]]\n[[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid Club de F\u00fatbol]] is a Spanish professional [[association football]] club based in [[Madrid]]. The club was formed in 1902 as ''Madrid Football Club'', and played its first competitive match on [[1902 Copa de la Coronaci\u00f3n|13 May 1902]], when it entered the semi-final of the [[Copa del Rey|Campeonato de Copa de S.M. Alfonso XIII]].<ref name=\"Real Madrid turns 106 (I)\">{{cite web | title = Pre-history and first official title (1900\u20131910) | url = http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/en/1202730681095/noticia/Noticia/Real_Madrid_turns_106_(I).htm | publisher = Realmadrid.com | accessdate = 12 July 2008 | author = Lu\u00eds Miguel Gonz\u00e1lez | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081229094130/http://www.realmadrid.com/cs/Satellite/en/1202730681095/noticia/Noticia/Real_Madrid_turns_106_%28I%29.htm | archivedate = 29 December 2008 | df = dmy-all }}</ref> Real Madrid currently plays in the Spanish La Liga. Real Madrid was one of the founding members of La Liga in [[1929 La Liga|1929]], and is one of three clubs, including [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] and [[Athletic Bilbao]], never to have been relegated from the league. They have also been involved in European football ever since they became the first Spanish club to enter the European Cup in 1955, except for the 1977\u201378 and [[1996\u201397 Real Madrid CF season|1996\u201397]] seasons.\n\nThis list encompasses the major honours won by Real Madrid and records set by the club, their managers and their players. The player records section includes details of the club's leading goalscorers and those who have made most appearances in first-team competitions. It also records notable achievements by Real Madrid players on the international stage, and the highest transfer fees paid and received by the club.\n\nThe club currently holds the record for the most [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup / UEFA Champions League]] triumphs with 13, and the most La Liga titles with 33. Real Madrid is also the most successful club in international titles with 26, more than any team in the world. The club's record appearance maker is [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]], who made 741 appearances from 1994 to 2010; the club's record goalscorer is Portuguese ace [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], who has 450 goals in all competitions.\n\n== Players ==\n{{See also|List of Real Madrid CF players}}\n\n=== Appearances ===\n''Competitive, professional matches only. Bold indicates player is still active at club level.''\n''As of 8 March 2020''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; width:70%;\"\n!!!Name!!Years!![[La Liga|League]]!![[Copa del Rey|Cup]]!!Europe{{ref label|Europe|A|}}!!Other{{ref label|Other|B|}}!!Total\n|-\n|1||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]]||1994\u20132010||550||37||132||22||'''741'''\n|-\n|2||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Iker Casillas]]||1999\u20132015||510||40||152||23||'''725'''\n|-\n|3||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Manuel Sanch\u00eds Hontiyuelo|Manuel Sanch\u00eds]]||1983\u20132001||523||67||100||20||'''710'''\n|-\n|4||{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Santillana (footballer)|Santillana]]||1971\u20131988||461||84||87||13||'''645'''\n|-\n|5||{{flagicon|ESP}} '''[[Sergio Ramos]]'''||2005\u2013''present''||445||48||124||24||'''640'''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|6||{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Fernando Hierro]]||1989\u20132003||439||43||103||16||'''601'''\n|-\n||{{flagicon|ESP|1945}}