th 50 or more international goals|international goals]] (total): '''99''' \u2013 [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], {{fb-rt|POR}}\n*Most international goals as a Real Madrid player: '''63''' \u2013 [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], {{fb-rt|POR}}\n;World Cup Winners\nThe following players have won the [[FIFA World Cup]] while playing for Real Madrid:<ref>https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/07/the-eleven-madridista-world-cup-winners</ref>\n\n* {{flagicon|GER}} [[G\u00fcnter Netzer]] ([[1974 FIFA World Cup|West Germany 1974]])\n* {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Jorge Valdano]] ([[1986 FIFA World Cup|Mexico 1986]])\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Christian Karembeu]] ([[1998 FIFA World Cup|France 1998]])\n* {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Roberto Carlos]] ([[2002 FIFA World Cup|South Korea/Japan 2002]])\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Iker Casillas]] ([[2010 FIFA World Cup|South Africa 2010]])\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ra\u00fal Albiol]] ([[2010 FIFA World Cup|South Africa 2010]])\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Xabi Alonso]] ([[2010 FIFA World Cup|South Africa 2010]])\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Sergio Ramos]] ([[2010 FIFA World Cup|South Africa 2010]])\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Alvaro Arbeloa]] ([[2010 FIFA World Cup|South Africa 2010]])\n* {{flagicon|GER}} [[Sami Khedira]] ([[2014 FIFA World Cup|Brazil 2014]])\n* {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Rapha\u00ebl Varane]] ([[2018 FIFA World Cup|Russia 2018]])\n\n=== Award winners ===\n;Ballon d'Or (1956\u20132009, 2016\u2013)\nThe following players have won the [[Ballon d'Or]] while playing for Real Madrid:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/europa-poy.html |title=European Footballer of the Year (\"Ballon d'Or\") |publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |date=9 October 2008 |accessdate=11 June 2010}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|ESP|1945}} [[Alfredo Di St\u00e9fano]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[1957 Ballon d'Or|1957]], [[1959 Ballon d'Or|1959]]\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Raymond Kopa]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[1958 Ballon d'Or|1958]]\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Lu\u00eds Figo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2000 Ballon d'Or|2000]]\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2002 Ballon d'Or|2002]]\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Fabio Cannavaro]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2006 Ballon d'Or|2006]]\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2013 FIFA Ballon d'Or|2013]], [[2014 FIFA Ballon d'Or|2014]], [[2016 Ballon d'Or|2016]], [[2017 Ballon d'Or|2017]]\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Luka Modri\u0107]] \u2013 [[2018 Ballon d'Or|2018]]\n;FIFA World Player of the Year (1991\u20132009)\nThe following players have won the [[FIFA World Player of the Year]] award while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Lu\u00eds Figo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2001 FIFA World Player of the Year|2001]]\n*{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2002 FIFA World Player of the Year|2002]]\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Zinedine Zidane]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2003 FIFA World Player of the Year|2003]]\n*{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Fabio Cannavaro]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2006 FIFA World Player of the Year|2006]]\n;FIFA Ballon d'Or (2010\u20132015)\nThe following players have won the [[FIFA Ballon d'Or]] while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[2013 FIFA Ballon d'Or|2013]], [[2014 FIFA Ballon d'Or|2014]]\n;The Best FIFA Men's Player (2016\u2013)\nThe following players have won [[the Best FIFA Men's Player]] while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2016|2016]], [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2017|2017]]\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Luka Modri\u0107]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2018|2018]]\n;European Golden Shoe\nThe following players have won the [[European Golden Shoe]] while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|MEX}} [[Hugo S\u00e1nchez]] &nbsp;\u2013 1990 (38 goals)\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] &nbsp;\u2013 2011 (40 goals), 2014 (31 goals), 2015 (48 goals)\n;UEFA Club Footballer of the Year (1998\u20132010)\nThe following players have won the [[UEFA Club Footballer of the Year]] award while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|ARG}} [[Fernando Redondo]]&nbsp;\u2013 2000\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Zinedine Zidane]]&nbsp;\u2013 2002\n;UEFA Best Player in Europe Award (2011\u2013)\nThe following players have won the [[UEFA Best Player in Europe Award]] while playing for Real Madrid:\n*{{flagicon|POR}} [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]&nbsp;\u2013 2014, 2016, 2017\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Luka Modri\u0107]]&nbsp;\u2013 2018\n\n=== Transfers ===\n\n==== Highest transfer fees paid ====\n[[File:Gareth Bale RM.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Gareth Bale]], signed in September 2013 from [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] for \u00a386 million, became Real Madrid's most expensive purchase.]]\nReal Madrid's record signings are Gareth Bale and Eden Hazard. Bale, who signed for the club from [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] for a fee which according to media reports is \u00a386 million in September 2013. Hazard, who signed from [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for a fee of \u00a389 million in July 2019.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!\n!Player\n!From\n!Transfer Fee<br />([[British Pound|\u00a3]] millions)<ref name=\"History of the world transfer record\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/8085391.stm |title=History of the world transfer record | date=11 June 2009 |accessdate=6 August 2009 |publisher=BBC Sport }}</ref><ref name=\"transfers\">{{cite web|url=http://www.footballtransfers.co.uk/transfers/rectrans.php |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070825144402/http://www.footballtransfers.co.uk/transfers/rectrans.php |archivedate=25 August 2007 |title=World's Highest Transfer Fees |publisher=Web.archive.org |date=25 August 2007 |accessdate=25 September 2013}}</ref>\n!Transfer Fee ([[Euro|\u20ac]] millions)\n!Date\n!Ref\n|-\n|1||{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Gareth Bale]]||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[TOTTENHAM HOTSPUR |Tottenham Hotspur]]||\u00a386||\u20ac100||September 2014||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/world-match-centre/news/newsid/219/598/0/index.html?|title=F\u00e9d